<p>What is the solution to <m>\displaystyle{10}{x}+{4}={4}{x}+{16}</m>? <fillin characters="3" />Preview Question 1 Â  </p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>2</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{10}{x}+{4}={4}{x}+{16}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}{x}+{4}-{16}={4}{x}+{16}-{16}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}{x}-{12}={4}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}{x}-{12}-{10}{x}={4}{x}-{10}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{12}=-{6}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{12}}{{-{{6}}}}=\frac{{-{6}{x}}}{{-{{6}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}={x}</m>.</p>

</solution>
